==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nebulosity
<hw>Neb`u*los"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
nebulositas: cf. F. <ets>n⟦eacute⟧bulosit⟦eacute⟧</ets>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality of being nebulous; cloudiness;
haziness; mistiness; nebulousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>nebulosity</qex> . . . of the mother idiom.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Disraeli.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The stuff of which
a nebula is formed.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A nebula.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nebulous</ent>⟦br⟧
